  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>basmati rice</strong>, <strong>cardamom pod[s] </strong>and 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[320ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-12 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked, then remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680278463222-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680278463222-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680278463222-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680278463222-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1680278463222-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Drain and rinse your <strong>chickpeas</strong>, then add them to a large bowl with <strong>half</strong> your<strong> garam masala</strong>, <strong>half</strong> your <strong>curry powder</strong> and<strong> half</strong> your <strong>cultured coconut </strong>(save the rest for later!)</p><p>Season with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and<strong> pepper</strong> and mix it all together</p><p>Add the <strong>spiced chickpeas </strong>to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray and place in the oven for 12-15 min or until the chickpeas are starting to char – these are your <strong>tandoori chickpeas</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680278468002-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680278468002-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680278468002-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680278468002-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1680278468002-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> and <strong>half </strong>the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) to a small bowl with a large knob of <strong>butter </strong>and stir it all together – this is your <strong>plant-based garlic & coriander butter</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680278473942-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680278473942-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680278473942-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680278473942-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1680278473942-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil </strong>over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced shallot</strong> with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p><p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>in 200ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [260ml] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong> – this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong> and pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680278479421-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680278479421-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680278479421-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680278479421-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1680278479421-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add your <strong>ginger & garlic paste</strong>, <strong>remaining garam masala </strong>and <strong>remaining curry powder </strong>to the pan and cook for a further 1 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add the <strong>tomato stock </strong>and cook for 4-5 min or until the sauce has thickened</p><p>Once thickened, remove the pan from the heat and stir through the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>cultured coconut</strong>, <strong>tandoori chickpeas </strong>(reserve the tray) and <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>chopped coriander </strong>– this is your<strong> chickpea curry</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680278482958-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680278482958-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680278482958-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680278482958-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1680278482958-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>To make the perfect burrito, top each <strong>tortilla</strong> with some <strong>spinach</strong>, <strong>cardamom rice</strong> and <strong>chickpea curry</strong>, fold the sides of each tortilla in and wrap the bottom of the tortilla over the filling, tucking it in tightly</p><p>Roll your <strong>tortilla </strong>until you’re left with a <strong>burrito </strong>– these are your <strong>chickpea burritos</strong></p><p>Tip: Go light on the filling on your first one so that you don't overfill the burritos!</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1680278486540-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1680278486540-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1680278486540-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1680278486540-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-6-1680278486540-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chickpea burritos</strong> to the reserved baking tray and put in the oven for 6-8 min or until lightly browned and crisp</p><p>Once browned, remove the tray from the oven and spread the <strong>plant-based garlic & coriander butter</strong> over the burritos – these are your <strong>plant-based garlic & coriander butter chickpea burritos</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1680278490586-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-7-1680278490586-x400.jpg",
